name: market for operation, dried roughage store, non ventilated | operation, dried roughage store, non ventilated | Cutoff, U
description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/4006/documentation

This is a market activity. Each market represents the consumption mix of a product in a given geography, connecting suppliers with consumers of the same product in the same geographical area. Markets group the producers and also the imports of the product (if relevant) within the same geographical area. They also account for transport to the consumer and for the losses during that process, when relevant.;This is the market for  'operation, dried roughage store, non ventilated', in the Global geography.;This market contains no transport or losses, as they are irrelevant for the delivered product.;This is delivering the service of 'operation, dried roughage store, non ventilated' referring to 1 kg of dry matter of final product of hay. It includes expenditures of infrastructure (storage facility) and electricity consumption necessary for the process. A user can employ the right amount of this process by matching the amount of dry matter (DM) in the hay he/she wishes to model with an equal amount of this process.

This activity starts with the service generation.


This activity ends with the service supplied to its consumers. Transport or losses are considered irrelevant for this product.
